<br>
one thought that i would like to give you: i think from the last 5 guilds on the vox rotation 4 failed to kill her, the 5th one didn't even try. maybe my loot rule was not great for everyone BUT you had loot to roll on. also there was only 33 rolling for loot, not 40 like on many vox raids.<br>
<br>
the good and bad points about me are a package deal, you get both or none and i think a dead vox with a not so great loot rule is better than a good loot rule with an alive vox. <br>
<br>
after all, no matter what loot rule we used, there was 4 items to be distributed amongst 33 people... this didn't change.<br>
<br>
pls have the others who disagreed also post their views here, i'm always trying to improve my raids and loot rules... IMO this was fairest loot rule that i can make, i am willing to accept critisism though. <br>
<br>
so far there was always complaints about loot (no matter the loot rule) on every low lvl raid and also on most high lvl raids that i've been leading so i got used to it. <p>Baroness Camala Ironarm<BR>
